Read the [Javadoc of `javax.faces.model.ResultSetDataModel`][1]:

&gt; public class ResultDataModel extends DataModel&lt;SortedMap&lt;String,Object&gt;&gt;

So it is a datamodel for `SortedMap&lt;String, Object&gt;`. 

When we drill down into the [Javadoc for `java.util.SortedMap`][2], then we see this:

&gt; **All Superinterfaces:**  
&gt; Map&lt;K,V&gt;

It does thus absolutely not extend from [`HashMap`][3]. That would only give you a `java.lang.ClassCastException`.

Just use `SortedMap` or `Map` instead:

```java
Map&lt;String, String&gt; map = (Map&lt;String, String&gt;) product;
```

Or, better, declare the argument type as-is so that you don&#39;t need an additional line to cast:

```java
public void addCart(Map&lt;String, String&gt; product) {
    // ...
}
```

  [1]: https://jakarta.ee/specifications/platform/8/apidocs/javax/faces/model/resultdatamodel
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/SortedMap.html
  [3]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/HashMap.html

